&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to employ an Emergency Nurse Practitioner (ENP) within the Aneurin Bevan University Health Board (ABUHB).The ENP will work across the Minor Injury Units (MIU) at the Royal Gwent Hospital (RGH), Nevill Hall Hospital (NHH) Ysbyty Ystrad Fawr (YYF) and Ysbyty Aneurin Bevan (YAB).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertaking the role of an ENP provides excellent opportunities for any nurse with the relevant experience, academic credibility and self motivation to practice at an advanced level across adult and paediatric minor injury services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to employ an ENP who has experience of delivering care to the full scope of minor injury presentations and is able to autonomously assess, diagnose and manage both adult and paediatric patients. We are looking for a self-motivated and dynamic ENP who is able to work as part of a team, flexible and adaptable to the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 12 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
